    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>) | [4 Bryanston Street, London.]</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Surman</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>It might save time, if you would write to me at Down, telling me (1) your Christian name in full (2.) where born. (3) age (4) How long, exactly you lived with my brother (5) &amp; how long at your previous place, giving name &amp; address of the family.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway</hi> … <hi rend="italic">S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added by CD</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 (4)] ‘4’ <hi rend="italic">over illeg</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13569.xml">letter to Albert Günther, 19 December 1881</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13569.xml">letter to Albert Günther, 19 December 1881</ref>. CD was trying to help Surman apply for a post at the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8646.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">British Museum</ref>. </note>   
        </div>
    
